OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FCentral Belt
OL,6,Fand the south having a mainly dry
OL,7,Fevening and night. Argyll will be
OL,8,Fcloudier with a few showers. Fresh
OL,9,Fsouthwesterly winds along coastal
OL,10,FArgyll.
OL,11,
OL,12,CMonday:FDry in the south but a showers
OL,13,Facross Argyll, and the Central Belt at
OL,14,Ffirst. Some bright spells but rather
OL,15,Fcloudy.
OL,16,
OL,17,COutlook for Tuesday to Thursday:
OL,18,FScattered showers on Tuesday, slow
OL,19,Fmoving and heavy by afternoon. Drier
OL,20,Fon Wednesday with fewer showers. Early
OL,21,Frain on Thursday then dry.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
